Interface Neighborhood<T>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of the vertex ID
All Known Implementing Classes:
PowerofTwo, UnrolledSkipList
public interface Neighborhood<T>
Neighborhood is an interface representing the neighborhood structure for a vertex. It provides methods for adding, removing, and retrieving neighbors, as well as finding intersections with other neighborhoods. This interface is implemented by both PowerOfTwoVector and UnrolledSkipList for handling small and large neighborhoods, respectively.
